SIMPLE: ringer
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ringer
<hw>Ring"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, rings; especially, one who rings chimes on
bells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>A crowbar.</def>
<rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ringer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ringer
<hw>Ring"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Horse Racing)</fld>
<def>A horse that is not entitled to take part in a race, but is
fraudulently got into it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ringhead</ent>⟦br⟧
